      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Tom Truscott</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:173px;\"><a href=\"http://www.heimo.de/jpool/articles/Geschichte.html\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/9/9d/Truscott.jpg\" width=\"171\" height=\"187\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Truscott.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Tom Truscott <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Thomas Robert (Tom) Truscott</b> (born 1953),<br />\nan American computer scientist, best known for creating the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Usenet\">Usenet</a> along with <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_Ellis_%28computing%29\">Jim Ellis</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/Steven_M._Bellovin\" title=\"Steven M. Bellovin\">Steven M. Bellovin</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. As graduate student at the <a href=\"/Duke_University\" title=\"Duke University\">Duke University</a> in the 70s, Truscott was early <a href=\"/Checkers\" title=\"Checkers\">Checkers</a> and chess programmer. The <i>Duke program</i> was a Checkers player written along with his fellow <a href=\"/Eric_Jensen\" title=\"Eric Jensen\">Eric Jensen</a> and advisor <a href=\"/Alan_Biermann\" title=\"Alan Biermann\">Alan Biermann</a>, which defeated <a href=\"/Arthur_Samuel\" title=\"Arthur Samuel\">Samuel's</a> program in a 2-game match <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>. Along with Eric Jensen and <a href=\"/Bruce_Wright\" title=\"Bruce Wright\">Bruce Wright</a>, Tom Truscott wrote the chess program <a href=\"/Duchess\" title=\"Duchess\">Duchess</a>, which competed at <a href=\"/ACM_North_American_Computer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"ACM North American Computer Chess Championship\">ACM North American Computer Chess Championships</a> from 1974 to 1979 and 1981, and the 2nd and 3rd <a href=\"/World_Computer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"World Computer Chess Championship\">World Computer Chess Championship</a> in <a href=\"/WCCC_1977\" title=\"WCCC 1977\">Toronto 1977</a> and <a href=\"/WCCC_1980\" title=\"WCCC 1980\">Linz 1980</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>. Tom Truscott now works for SAS <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>, an analytics software company <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> . \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Photos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Photos</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Usenet_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Usenet Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Photos\">Photos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Truscott&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Photos\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://www.computerhistory.org/chess/full_record.php?iid=stl-430b9bbe2be7f\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Chaos vs Duchess.ACM 1979.jpg\" src=\"/images/d/d4/Chaos_vs_Duchess.ACM_1979.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"447\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div> \n<p><a href=\"/CHAOS\" title=\"CHAOS\">CHAOS</a> vs. <a href=\"/Duchess\" title=\"Duchess\">Duchess</a> at the <a href=\"/ACM_1979\" title=\"ACM 1979\">ACM 1979</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/David_Cahlander\" title=\"David Cahlander\">David Cahlander</a>, <a href=\"/William_Toikka\" title=\"William Toikka\">William Toikka</a>, <a href=\"/Fred_Swartz\" title=\"Fred Swartz\">Fred Swartz</a> and Tom Truscott \n</p>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://www.computerhistory.org/collections/accession/102665753\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Chess Pioneers Mittman Newborn Marsland Slate Levy Shannon Thompson Truscott.c1980.102665753.lg.jpg\" src=\"/images/c/c2/Chess_Pioneers_Mittman_Newborn_Marsland_Slate_Levy_Shannon_Thompson_Truscott.c1980.102665753.lg.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"512\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div> \n<p>Chess pioneers in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_Sacher\">Sacher Hotel Vienna</a>, Austria 1980: <a href=\"/Ben_Mittman\" title=\"Ben Mittman\">Ben Mittman</a>, <a href=\"/Monroe_Newborn\" title=\"Monroe Newborn\">Monty Newborn</a>, <a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a>,<br /><a href=\"/David_Slate\" title=\"David Slate\">Dave Slate</a>, <a href=\"/David_Levy\" title=\"David Levy\">David Levy</a>, <a href=\"/Claude_Shannon\" title=\"Claude Shannon\">Claude Shannon</a>, <a href=\"/Ken_Thompson\" title=\"Ken Thompson\">Ken Thompson</a>, Betty Shannon, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Truscott</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Truscott&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>From <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Hauben\">Michael</a> and Ronda Hauben's netbook <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.columbia.edu/~hauben/project_book.html\">Netizens: On the History and Impact of Usenet and the Internet</a></i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>:\n</p>\n<pre><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Truscott</a> and <a href=\"/Bruce_Wright\" title=\"Bruce Wright\">Wright</a> continued to participate in the Chess Tournaments and in 1980 they competed in the 3rd world Computer Chess Championship held in Linz, Austria. <a href=\"/Ken_Thompson\" title=\"Ken Thompson\">Thompson</a> and <a href=\"/Joe_Condon\" title=\"Joe Condon\">Joe Condon</a>, who was a researcher at <a href=\"/Bell_Laboratories\" title=\"Bell Laboratories\">Bell Labs</a>, were also in the competition. Truscott notes that Thompson and Condon \"had completed their hardware chess machine and snagged first place. <a href=\"/Duchess\" title=\"Duchess\">Duchess</a> came in third. And <a href=\"/Claude_Shannon\" title=\"Claude Shannon\">Claude Shannon</a> was in attendance, and even handed out the trophies at the awards ceremony. Afterwards we all went over to a TV studio to watch a West German TV special on computer chess and the championship. Claude Shannon and his wife were very engaging people. Someone took a photo of all of us, I have a copy buried somewhere\". \n</pre>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Truscott&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Truscott</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i>Computer-Checkers</i>. <a href=\"/Personal_Computing#2_9\" title=\"Personal Computing\">Personal Computing, Vol. 2, No. 9</a>, pp. 86 </li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Hauben\">Michael Hauben</a>, Ronda Hauben (<b>1997</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.columbia.edu/~hauben/project_book.html\">Netizens: On the History and Impact of Usenet and the Internet</a>.</i> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0818677066.html\">Wiley-IEEE Computer Society Press</a>, ISBN: 978-0-8186-7706-9 <sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Usenet_Posts\">Usenet Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Truscott&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Usenet Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://quux.org:70/Archives/usenet-a-news/NET.chess/82.01.05_duke.1553_net.chess.txt\">Re: sri-unix.426: compact representation of a position</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Truscott</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://quux.org:70/Archives/usenet-a-news/NET.chess\">net.chess</a>, January 5, 1982</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://quux.org:70/Archives/usenet-a-news/NET.chess/82.01.07_duke.1593_net.chess.txt\">Re: sri-unix.444: compact representation of chess positions</a> by  <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Truscott</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://quux.org:70/Archives/usenet-a-news/NET.chess\">net.chess</a>, January 7, 1982&#160;» <a href=\"/Zobrist_Hashing\" title=\"Zobrist Hashing\">Zobrist Hashing</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Truscott&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Truscott\">Tom Truscott from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Duke_University_people\">List of Duke University people from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=435\">Tom Truscott's ICGA Tournaments</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.newsdemon.com/tom-truscott-usenet-founder.php\">Newsdemon - Tom Truscott Biography</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Truscott&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.heimo.de/jpool/articles/Geschichte.html\">Die Geschichte des Internet</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.heimo.de/jpool/index.html\">Heimo Ponnath</a> (German)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Truscott\">Tom Truscott from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.cs.columbia.edu/~smb/informal-bio.html\">Steven M. Bellovin - Bio</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1928&amp;dat=19770512&amp;id=hr4gAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=xmkFAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=4778,1673986\">The Lewiston Daily Sun - Google News Archive</a>, May 12, 1977</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fierz.ch/history.htm\">A brief history of computer checkers</a> by <a href=\"/Martin_Fierz\" title=\"Martin Fierz\">Martin Fierz</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://checkersbackground.com/samuel-s-and-the.html\">Samuel's and The Duke Checkers Programs</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=435\">Tom Truscott's ICGA Tournaments</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sas.com/\">SAS | Business Analytics and Business Intelligence Software</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.giganews.com/usenet-history/truscott.html\">Interview with Tom Truscott</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.giganews.com/\">giganews.com</a> April 18, 2007</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.computerhistory.org/chess/full_record.php?iid=stl-430b9bbe2be7f\">Chaos vs. Duchess</a> at the <a href=\"/ACM_1979\" title=\"ACM 1979\">10th ACM North American Computer Chess Championship</a>, 1979 Gift of <a href=\"/Monroe_Newborn\" title=\"Monroe Newborn\">Monroe Newborn</a> from <a href=\"/The_Computer_History_Museum\" title=\"The Computer History Museum\">The Computer History Museum</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.computerhistory.org/collections/accession/102665753\">Chess pioneers in Sacher Hotel Vienna, Austria</a>, Gift of <a href=\"/Ben_Mittman\" title=\"Ben Mittman\">Benjamin Mittman</a>, <a href=\"/The_Computer_History_Museum\" title=\"The Computer History Museum\">The Computer History Museum</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.columbia.edu/~rh120/ch106.x10\">Chapter 10 - On the early days of Usenet: The Roots of the cooperative Online Culture</a> a draft chapter from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Hauben\">Michael Hauben</a>, Ronda Hauben (<b>1997</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.columbia.edu/~hauben/project_book.html\">Netizens: On the History and Impact of Usenet and the Internet</a>.</i> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0818677066.html\">Wiley-IEEE Computer Society Press</a>, ISBN: 978-0-8186-7706-9</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.columbia.edu/~rh120/ch106.x10\">Chapter 10 - On the early days of Usenet: The Roots of the cooperative Online Culture</a> a draft chapter</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-14\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-14\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/a0a82ffbb59b7ced\">Re: Hashing function for board positions</a> post 4 by <a href=\"/James_Gillogly\" title=\"James Gillogly\">Jim Gillogly</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, May 12, 1997</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 202603011